FBIS4-9470 "dreeu080__a94039" FBIS-EEU-94-080-A Daily Report 26 April 1994 ANNEX Poland Deliveries to Plants To Continue Deliveries to Plants To Continue LD2604115294 Warsaw PAP in English 1118 GMT 26 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY LD2604115294 Warsaw PAP English BFN [Text] Piotrkow Trybunalski, April 26 -- The All-Poland Strike Committee of the brown coal mines agreed on Tuesday [26 April] to deliver coal in quantities sufficient to generate some 25 percent of the energy generated by individual power plants. The decision was announced following industry minister's declaration during talks with union leaders here that he is cancelling orders concerning the restructuring of the brown coal sector. Spokesman for Solidarity's national commission said that the decision on resumption of coal deliveries will be lifted at 2000 hrs on Thursday if the government side fails to adopt a time-table, approved by Solidarity, of dealing with the demands put forward by the union.
